 Indicators in trading

    Console-based C++17 visualization example of a RSI (Relative Strength Index) trading indicator.

    Momentum Indicators
        Measure the speed of price movement.
 
        eg. RSI (Relative Strength Index)	
                Measures overbought/oversold (70 = overbought, 30 = oversold).

            RSI Calculation Basics

                RSI = 100 - (100 / (1 + RS))

                    RS = Average Gain / Average Loss (over N periods)

